splitdnsd (0.3.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Local plane trust tiers: a TSIG/peer-cred (strong) mDNS announcement now creates a
    persistent, shadow-immune trusted allocation that survives host-down and cannot be
    displaced by a self-announced address; a trusted_sources source IP stays weak (DDNS
    trigger only). New [mdns] trusted_grace + max_trusted knobs.
  * Search-list collision recovery: host.lan.<zone> / host.<zone>.lan resolve from the
    local plane under the queried name, never the public wildcard (closes the
    "<host>.lan -> public IP" leak). Restricted (vhost/DDNS) names serve the trusted tier
    only; unrestricted names serve their self-announced address on every spelling.

 -- gutschke <gutschke@users.noreply.github.com>  Tue, 08 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0700

splitdnsd (0.2.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix splitdns-notify-relay.socket run-dir perms (DirectoryMode 0750 -> 0755) so a
    writer in group splitdns-notify can traverse it to the socket; the relay service is
    now Type=exec to avoid a readiness-handshake hang.

 -- gutschke <gutschke@users.noreply.github.com>  Fri, 04 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0700

splitdnsd (0.2.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * splitdns-notify: socket-activated relay (--listen) + built-in client (--relay)
    so an unprivileged DHCP lease hook can trigger a signed announce without the TSIG
    key or a socat dependency. Ships splitdns-notify-relay.socket/.service and a Kea
    hook example.

 -- gutschke <gutschke@users.noreply.github.com>  Fri, 04 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0700

splitdnsd (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Encrypted client DNS (DoT/DoH) with DDR auto-upgrade advertising (opt-in).
  * Local plane: .lan/.local names from mDNS, on-demand resolution, unicast DNS-SD.
  * Diagnostics console: mDNS host enrichment, Encrypted & DDR panel, transport query tool.
  * Security hardening: diagnostics control CSRF header, TSIG replay protection.

